The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 CA receives ICC reward

Sydney: Cricket Australia (CA) received a $500,000 cheque on Tuesday from the International Cricket Council (ICC) in recognition of the countrys position at the top of the ICC championship tables up to April this year. 

CA chief executive James Sutherland, who received the cheque, paid tribute to the performance of the Australian team and the administrative bodies that support the players off the field. 

Lehmann vetoed 

Meanwhile in Adelaide, former Test batsman Darren Lehmann on Tuesday said he was vetoed by Cricket Australia (CA) for a position on the Australian selection panel left vacant by Allan Border because he plans to carry on playing cricket. (Agencies) 




